      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tapering warfarin on your own is a dangerous gamble, and I strongly advise against it. The worst-case scenario for dropping the dose without monitoring is that your blood may become too thick, leading to a serious blood clot. Since you are feeling well, you might be in a safe zone, but that zone is constantly shifting and requires professional oversight. For your safety, you must maintain your current dose until your doctor can reassess your needs.",
